added.title: Sheep Bears
added.description: The Bears get jobs as sheep herders on an idyllic farm.

added.title: Ice Bear's Pet
added.description: Ice Bear attempts to keep a giant owl-monster secretly as a pet.

added.title: Dragon Pests
added.description: The Bears and Squatter Otter crash a couple's swanky pad while they're out of town.

added.title: No Land, All Air!
added.description: The Bears find themselves in a world of dog fighting planes and floating airships.

added.title: Tooth Fairy Tech
added.description: In order to earn enough money to buy a house, the Bears work as tooth fairies.

added.title: Exercising the Demons
added.description: When a severe screen addiction turns the kids into lazy deadbeats, Chef brings in a professional to whip them into shape.

added.title: Pudding the Planet First
added.description: Chef accidentally cooks up a killer cyborg turkey in a failed attempt to get the kids to appreciate him on Appreciation Day.

added.title: Supply Mom
added.description: When Chef's mom becomes the supply teacher for a day Duncan replaces Chef's to-do list with one of his own.

added.title: Mooshy Mon Mons
added.description: After eating Chef's extremely rare and expensive chocolates Courtney drags Owen, Izzy and Beth all the way to the Norberian Alps of Fruffenberg to replace them.

added.title: Student Becomes the Teacher
added.description: Chef is knocked unconscious right before a School Board Evaluator shows up for a big review. Now Owen has to fill in so Chef doesn't lose his Teaching License and to ensure the kids earn the pony ride Chef promised for good behavior.

added.title: Bone Head/Relax
added.description: A dog uncovers trouble when he buries a bone in Bugs Bunny's hole. Porky Pig wants to relax, but his nephew Cicero is visiting.

added.title: Rotund Rabbit/Hog Wash
added.description: After stuffing himself with carrots, a big, round Bugs rolls over Elmer. Porky Pig takes a very painful trip through an automated car wash.

added.title: Funhouse
added.description: The Tennysons find themselves stuck inside an inescapable funhouse constructed by Zombozo; Ben goes alien and fights for escape, ultimately proving that behind every illusion, there's a disappointing secret.

added.title: Summer Breakers
added.description: After Grandpa Max's super smart buddy Phil discovers that a second extraterrestrial item crashed alongside the Omnitrix, Team Tennyson sets off to find the second crash site before someone else does but arrive instead to find nefarious newcomer Breaker One-Nine has already beat them to the punch.

added.title: The Monsters in Your Head
added.description: Ben and Gwen learn a rumor of an alien invasion happening at the park they are camping at, but when they investigate, they discover a preserve containing a host of mutated creatures engineered by Animo! With the unexpected help of Kevin 11 and his family, Ben proves that the rumors are false, and that truth is stranger than fiction!

added.title: Queen of Bees
added.description: Ben, Gwen and Grandpa Max arrive in Bismarck, North Dakota for its annual celebration of bee pollination, bringing them face-to-face with Queen Bee and a bold new scheme, forcing Ben to conquer his new fear of bees!

added.title: Gentle Ben
added.description: Grandpa Max's alma mater asks him to use the Omni-Copter to transport an important exhibit to an exotic nature reserve, but when the exhibit turns out to be a rare and very large baby moth, Ben must keep Tim Buktu from stealing the moth while learning that sometimes you need to use finesse and not force to solve hard problems.

added.title: The Galactic Enforcers
added.description: Ben joins a trio of intergalactic alien heroes tracking down the bounty hunter Six Six. But this bunch of heroes is not all it's cracked up to be.

added.title: Camp Fear
added.description: When a race of alien mushrooms takes over a summer camp, Ben discovers a whole new alien to battle the menace.

added.title: Ultimate Weapon
added.description: When Max finds out that part of an alien weapon has been unearthed in Texas, he becomes obsessed with finding it. In doing so, he leads Ben and Gwen on a wild adventure.

added.title: Tough Luck
added.description: Gwen's Lucky Girl powers return when she buys a magical stone at a magic convention in Las Vegas. However, Hex is after the same stone, and after his niece breaks him out of prison, the two set off to retrieve the stone.

added.title: They Lurk Below
added.description: Max's old friend has built the world's only underwater resort, and Ben, Gwen and Max are invited for a sneak peak. But it turns out in order to power the resort, Max's friend took an energy orb from a race of underwater aliens. Now, the aliens want their energy orb back and destroy the resort in order to get it.

added.title: Arrested Development
added.description: Ben and Rook must stop the evil Robots from Dimension 12 while trapped in their own pre-pubescent bodies, thanks to Ben's childhood rival.  (Introducing Billy Billions.)

added.title: Bros in Space
added.description: Rook brings Ben to his home planet to meet the family. Unbeknownst to them, an old foe is raising an army to steal the planet's most precious resource!  (Introducing Rook's family.)

added.title: Ben Again
added.description: When Eon causes 11-year old Ben swap minds with teen Ben, it's up to Gwen, Rook, and Professor Paradox to set things straight.  (Featuring Eon and Professor Paradox.)

added.title: Store 23
added.description: While out looking for the elusive 23rd Mr. Smoothy's store with Blukic and Driba, Ben meets an alternate version of himself.

added.title: Special Delivery
added.description: As payment for destroying his car, Mr. Bowman orders Ben to make deliveries for him without using the Omnitrix.  (Featuring Thunderpig, new Ben alien Toepick.)

added.title: The Maze of the Red Dragon
added.description: Still in the game zone Terra Kerana, the Samurai guide Okino has to choose between helping his allies the ninja, or obeying the evil orders of his Master, Unagami.

added.title: One Step Forward, Two Steps Back
added.description: When the ninja learn that the only way to acquire the second Key-tana is by winning a dangerous race in Terra Technica they'll have to find some racing cars in unexpected ways.

added.title: Racer Seven
added.description: As the ninja prepare for the brutal Speedway Five-Billion race, Lloyd meets a race driver named Seven, who is programmed to lose, but who may hold the key to victory.

added.title: The Speedway Five-Billion
added.description: Unagami's soldiers, the Red Visors, finally discover the secret location of Scott's garage and attack the ninja, who manage to escape with the help of Racer Seven, and enter the spectacular Speedway Five Billion.

added.title: Stop, Drop and Side Scroll
added.description: Our ninja barely have time to mourn the loss of their fallen ninja friends before being thrust into the madness of Terra Domina where Lloyd will have to face an old adversary from his past.

added.title: The Best Friend/Thief and Brawler
added.description: The Best Friend: The top four brawlers in the Bakugan Battle League have been decided. For this round of the semi-finals it's a battle of best friends: Wynton vs. Dan. The winner of this battle between best buddies will move on to the championship round./Thief and Brawler: In the final battle of the Bakugan Battle league semi-finals it's Shun vs. Ajit. It's a grueling battle of focus, will, and strength, only a true brawler to emerge victorious.

added.title: Final Battle! Dan vs. Ajit/Secrets Exposed
added.description: Final Battle! Dan vs. Ajit: It's time for the event everyone in Los Volmos has been waiting for, The Bakugan Battle League finals! It's the Awesome Brawler's Dan Kouzo vs. the golden Bakugan brawler Ajit, these two face-off in a final brawl for it all./Secrets Exposed: The Bakugan Battle League has ended, and the winner has been determined, but the celebration is cut short when Phantom Thief Storm crashes the party by stealing everyone's Bakugan! It's up to Dan and Ajit to stop Storm and return all the stolen Bakugan.

added.title: Here Comes Haavik/The Fusion Bakugan Arrive
added.description: Here Comes Haavik: An evil shapeshifting alien has landed in Los Volmos! If that wasn't bad enough, he has a group of robot mechanoids on his trail trying to bring him justice. Meanwhile, Dan has accepted a battle challenge from a pair of brawlers, Chad and Trey./The Fusion Bakugan Arrive: Still humiliated by their defeat, Chad and Trey challenge Dan to rematch but this time they have a few tricks up their sleeve, and a little help on their side.

added.title: The Director/Queen Ebony
added.description: The Director: Everett Ray reaches out to Lia with an opportunity that seems too good to be true. Everett is now working in show business and proposes to make Lia's dream of becoming a film director come true. He's taken care of all the arrangements; all Lia has to do is provide the directorial vision./Queen Ebony: On his daily jaunt, Lightning learns of a street cat named Ebony, who's been treating dogs like servants, threatening them to do her bidding or face the wrath of her Bakugan! Lightning tries to reason with Ebony but when that doesn't work, it turns into a cat vs. dog Bakugan brawl!

added.title: Sophie, the Bakuganist/Midnight Train Battle!
added.description: Sophie, the Bakuganist: Magnus is on the trail of the illegal Baku-brawling devices and, is looking to cut off the supply at its source. When he witnesses an illegal deal going down, he knows it's up to him to go after the shipment to keep the illegal devices off the street./Midnight Train Battle!: Sophie Judson Warfield, a wealthy activist with the Citizens to Save Bakugan Society, is working to put an end to all Bakugan brawling. Her latest target is the Awesome Brawlers themselves. When Wynton doesn't take Sophie seriously, the encounter quickly turns into an all-out Bakugan brawl.

added.title: Calmado Ben
added.description: El alma máter del abuelo Max le pide que utilice el Omnicóptero para transportar una pieza muy importante a una reserva natural de especies exóticas. Pero cuando la pieza resulta ser una polilla bebé rara y muy grande, Ben debe evitar que Tim Buktu se la robe.

added.title: Casa de la Risa
added.description: Los Tennyson se encuentran atrapados dentro de una casa de la risa construida por Zombozo, de la cual es imposible escapar; Ben se vuelve alienígena y lucha por escapar, y así demuestra que, a fin de cuentas, detrás de cada ilusión hay un secreto decepcionante.

added.title: Interrumpiendo el Verano
added.description: Cuando Phil, el brillante amigo del abuelo Max, descubre que un segundo objeto extraterrestre se estrelló junto al Omnitrix, el equipo Tennyson se pone en marcha para encontrar el segundo lugar de la colisión antes de otro lo haga.

added.title: Los Monstruos de tu Cabeza
added.description: Ben y Gwen se enteran del rumor de una invasión alienígena en el parque en el que están acampando, pero cuando investigan, descubren una reserva que contiene una gran cantidad de criaturas mutantes diseñadas por Animo.

added.title: Reina de las Abejas
added.description: Ben, Gwen y el abuelo Max visitan Bismarck, en Dakota del Norte, para la celebración anual del festival de abejas. Al encontrarse cara a cara con Abeja Reina y su nuevo plan, Ben debe conquistar su nuevo miedo a las abejas.

added.title: Ejercitando los Demonios
added.description: Cuando una severa adicción a las pantalla convierte a los niños en holgazanes, Chef trae a una profesional para ponerlos en forma.

added.title: Pudin-Pocalipsis
added.description: Después de que Chef dice que los puntos de vista contrarios hacen al mundo más interesante y divertido, Izzy lo aplica del peor modo posible.

added.title: El Laberinto del Dragon Rojo
added.description: Aún en la zona de juego de Tierra Karana, Okino tiene que elegir entre ayudar a sus aliados ninjas, u obedecer las órdenes de su Maestro, Unagami.

added.title: Mama Suplente
added.description: Cuando la mamá de Chef se convierte en maestra suplente por un día, Duncan cambia la lista de actividades de Chef por la suya.

added.title: Un Paso Adelante, Dos Pasos Atras
added.description: La única manera de que los Ninjas obtengan segunda Keytana es ganando una carrera en Tierra Technica y tiene que conseguir autos de carreras para eso.

added.title: Mushi-Mon-Mon
added.description: Después de comer los muy costosos y raros chocolates de Chef, Courtney arrastra a Owen, Izzy y Beth hasta los Alpes Norberianos de Fruffenberg para reemplazarlos.

added.title: Piloto Siete
added.description: Mientras los Ninjas se preparan para la carrera Cinco Billones por Hora, Lloyd conoce a la Piloto Siete quien puede tener la clave de la victoria.

added.title: El Estudiante se Hace Maestro
added.description: Chef queda insconsciente justo antes de que una evaluadora de la junta escolar aparezca para una inspección. Ahora Owen tiene que reemplazarlo para que Chef no pierda su licencia de maestro y para asegurar que los chicos ganen el paseo en pony que Chef les prometió por su buena conducta.

added.title: Carrera Cinco Billones por Hora
added.description: Los soldados de Unagami, los Visores Rojos, finalmente descubren la ubicación secreta del garaje de Scott y atacan a los Ninjas.

added.title: Detenerse, Caer y Girar
added.description: Los Ninjas no han ni llorado la pérdida de sus amigos  caídos cuando ya deben entrar a la locura de Tierra Domina.

added.title: Buff's BFF
added.description: When Buff befriends Mr. Freeze's snowcrawler Snowy, the other Batwheels bristle at the thought of hanging out with a "bad guy…" so Buff sets out to change their minds.

added.title: Up in the Air
added.description: After he causes the Batwing to crash, Bam becomes obsessed with making it up to her during a high-stakes aerial mission against Penguin and his giant ducky blimp.

added.title: MacBarm's Day Off/Playhouse Problems
added.description: It's MacBarm's day off and Zee takes over harvesting carrots with his Zee mobile, but when it breaks, the work still needs to be done./Ranger Nat is bringing a playhouse on the train for Timmy and Izzy, but it won't fit through the tunnel!

added.title: Can't Stop the Martians/Best Nest Test
added.description: The Martians come to Pretty Big City but find themselves in need of help when they are unable to land their spaceship./Zee needs to communicate with Sif in outer space but can't because a bird has made its home on top of the satellite dish!

added.title: Sir Topham Hatt's Hat
added.description: When Sir Topham Hatt's Hat blows away in the wind before making an important announcement, Thomas and his friends race around Sodor, trying to catch it. The Hat remains out of reach until they learn to work together.
added.originalseriesname: Thomas and Friends: All Engines Go

added.title: Nia's Surprising Surprise
added.description: Nia is planning a big party to celebrate the anniversary of her arrival on Sodor, but she finds that her friends don't remember her anniversary and are too busy to even talk about it.
added.originalseriesname: Thomas and Friends: All Engines Go

added.title: A New View for Thomas
added.description: When Thomas spends the day carrying rockstar idol Harold across Sodor, he gains a new perspective on just how amazing it is to be his engine-self.
added.originalseriesname: Thomas and Friends: All Engines Go

added.title: Skiff Sails Sodor
added.description: When Skiff gets a crack in his hull, Thomas needs to move him overland to Harwick for repairs, but Skiff's land-sickness makes that challenging.
added.originalseriesname: Thomas and Friends: All Engines Go

added.title: Song of Sodor
added.description: When Nia suggests adding a song to spice up Sir Topham Hatt's new bench unveiling, he calls upon her to write a song for the ceremony, but Nia soon finds she may have bitten off more than she can sing.
added.originalseriesname: Thomas and Friends: All Engines Go

added.title: Gravity
added.description: Three, two, one, lift-off! On this mission to the moon, Blippi bounces around with Rocky the Moon Rock. Light as a feather they bound up and float back down, teaching Blippi all about gravity! One small step for Blippi, one giant leap for Blippi.

added.title: Honey
added.description: Blippi and FETCH shrink down and fly inside a very active beehive, where they meet Bijon, the fast-talking, fast-moving Worker Bee. With a talent for rhyming and making honey, Bijon rhymes her way through the sweet explanation of how delicious honey is made. What a very buzzy... erm...busy day!

added.title: Ocean
added.description: Blippi's trusty BlippiMobile safely transports him to a whole new underwater world! He dives into the sea, where he gets an ocean tour from a local resident, Jerry the Jellyfish. They swim through a huge kelp forest, explore the ocean floor and meet interesting underwater creatures along the way!

added.title: 5 Little Ducks - Playtime at the Farm!
added.description: Mia and Ella find a nest of baby ducks. Ella plays "Mummy Duck." Will they find their real mummy?

added.title: ABC Song - Learn Phonics
added.description: Dancing around the barn, characters pop up, each singing about a different letter of the alphabet.

added.title: Trick or Treat
added.description: Mei, Mummy and Ella (3 generations of the same family) are all trick or treating together around the CITY!
